  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislations\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorism Financing Act (Australia)\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Mandatory financial record-keeping\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Specific Requirements\n- Financial institutions must report large cash transactions\n- Background checks on customers\n- Risk assessment of financial activities\n- Mandatory employee training on detecting suspicious activities\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income through complex financial transactions.",
